<p itemprop="description">A service owner is responsible for the ongoing success of a digital service, ensuring it continues to meet user needs and business objectives. They work with delivery teams to maintain and improve services while managing stakeholder relationships and service performance.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Own the vision, strategy, and roadmap for the service</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure service meets user needs and performance standards</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Manage service budget and resource allocation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Work with delivery teams to maintain and improve the service</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Monitor service performance and user satisfaction</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Manage stakeholder relationships and expectations</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure service compliance with government standards and policies</li>
    </ul>
</section>

